title: Most of the Texas border buoys to deter migrants are actually in Mexican territory
description: Texas leaders have said they're experiencing an "invasion" at the border but buoys set up as barriers have breached Mexican territory, an international body found.

title: World Aquatics to debut 'open category' races for transgender swimmers in Berlin
description: The first “open category” swimming races to accommodate transgender competitors will take place at a World Cup event in Berlin in October, the sport’s governing body said Wednesday.

title: Man tried to burn memorial for gay victims of Nazis in Berlin, police say
description: Berlin police arrested a man Tuesday in an arson attack on the city’s Memorial to Homosexuals Persecuted Under Nazism.

title: Muslim mob attacks churches in Pakistan after accusing Christians of desecrating the Quran
description: Muslims in eastern Pakistan went on a rampage over allegations that a Christian man had desecrated the Quran, burning churches and damaging other homes.

title: England advances to Women’s World Cup final after beating Australia
description: Australia’s Women’s World Cup run came to end after the co-hosts were beaten 3 goals to 1 by England, who advanced to face Spain in the final. NBC News’ Molly Hunter reports.

title: Mexico's Claudia Sheinbaum grows her lead for ruling party presidential ticket
description: Former Mexico City Mayor Claudia Sheinbaum has grown her lead to be the ruling MORENA party’s candidate in Mexico’s 2024 presidential election, a poll found.

title: Watch: The Killers introduce a Russian fan on stage at a concert in Georgia
description: The Killers frontman Brandon Flowers was booed by members of the audience at a concert in a Black Sea resort in Georgia, after he introduced a Russian fan who had been invited to play on stage during the song "For Reasons Unknown."

title: England beats Australia 3-1 to move into Women’s World Cup final
description: England moved on to its first Women’s World Cup championship game with a 3-1 victory Wednesday over co-host Australia, ending the Matildas captivating run.

title: Video shows Ukrainian security service unveiling new sea drone
description: Ukraine's Security Service has released video of what it says is a maritime drone named "SeaBaby."

title: Tomatoes on ‘vacation,’ Burger King says as India battles food inflation
description: Burger King has scrapped tomatoes from its wraps and burgers in many outlets in India after prices more than quadrupled as food inflation surges.

title: 'Game of Thrones' actor Darren Kent has died, talent agency says
description: Darren Kent, best known for his roles in dramas like “Game of Thrones” and “EastEnders,” has died, his talent agency said.

title: The Killers apologize after boos for bringing Russian fan onstage
description: The Killers apologized Tuesday for bringing a Russian fan onstage at a concert in Georgia, met with boos by the audience.

title: India and China pledge to maintain ‘peace and tranquility’ along disputed border despite tensions
description: China and India pledged to “maintain the peace and tranquility” along their disputed border to stabilize the situation after a rise in tensions.

title: New Zealand jury finds mom guilty of killing her 3 young daughters in a case that shocked the nation
description: A New Zealand jury on Wednesday found a mother guilty of murdering her three young daughters in a case that shocked the nation.
